HTML5 microdata library

* Funtion

HTML5 microdata parser
 - Light weight streaming parser
   - Parse chunk html little by little, and when microdata is detected, the corresponding events are passed via registered callback handlers
   - Because currently the parser works on SAX parser and don't create huge DOM tree internally, applications can reduce the memory foot print
 - Data model builder
   - Create a data model for microdata based on the parsed result of underlying streaming parser
   - All microdata can be accessed via API
 - microdata API

* How to build
  - Make sure libxml is installed
  - Execute ./configure
  - Execute 'make' command

* Sample programs
  - Several samples can be found in $ROOT/examples/microdata

* API specification
  - Execute 'doxygen' command under $ROOT/csem
  - API documentation is serialized in $ROOT/doc as both html and man

